item.title: Problem i think its Windows 7 :[]
item.dc:creator: @server868 server868
item.description:
@server868 wrote:

jdk problem is easy.
Edit your compile.bat and you will see 2 addresses at the top
They are supposed to be the location of your jdk. You have to fix it to look like set pro=%programfiles%\Java\jdk1.6.0_16<---- Last # must be your java update #…

EDIT

I can help you via team-viewer if you need.
